Implemented Vercel Speed Insights for Static HTML Website

## Changes Made

### Modified:
- `index.html` - Added Vercel Speed Insights tracking scripts

## Implementation Details

This project is a static HTML website, so I implemented the HTML version of Vercel Speed Insights as per the official documentation.

### What was added:
Added two script tags before the closing `</body>` tag:
1. Initialization script that creates the `window.si` function and `window.siq` queue
2. Deferred script that loads the Speed Insights tracking from `/_vercel/speed-insights/script.js`

### Location:
The scripts were added at line 990-995 in index.html, right after the existing JavaScript files (main.js and premium.js) and before the closing body tag.

### Why this approach:
- For static HTML sites, no npm package installation is required
- The scripts are loaded with `defer` attribute for better performance
- The tracking script will be served by Vercel's CDN once the site is deployed to Vercel
- This follows the exact pattern specified in the Vercel Speed Insights documentation for HTML projects

### Next Steps:
Once this is deployed to Vercel:
1. Enable Speed Insights in the Vercel dashboard under the project's Speed Insights tab
2. The `/_vercel/speed-insights/script.js` route will be automatically available after deployment
3. Performance metrics will start being collected from visitors
4. Data will be viewable in the Vercel dashboard under the Speed Insights tab

### Notes:
- No dependencies were added (HTML implementation doesn't require @vercel/speed-insights package)
- No build process changes needed
- The implementation is lightweight and won't affect page load performance
- The script uses the defer attribute to ensure it doesn't block page rendering
